# Aero Templates

## Component Naming

Use `-component` or `-layout` suffix in markup; import without suffix (resolves to .html):

```html
<script on:build>
	import header from '@components/header'
</script>
<header-component title="Hello" />
```

## Script Types

- `<script on:build>` - Build time; has `aero.props`, `site`, imports
- `<script on:client>` - Bundled as virtual module, runs in browser
- `<script src="...">` - External scripts allowed without attributes
- **Required**: Inline scripts must have `on:client` or `on:build`

## Props

- Pass: attributes, `data-props="{ ...obj }"`, or `data-props` / `props` to spread a `props` variable
- Receive: destructure `aero.props` in `<script on:build>`

```html
<my-component title="{ site.title }" />
<my-component data-props />
<script on:build>
	const { title } = aero.props
</script>
```

## Loops and Slots

- Loops: `data-each="item in items"` then `{ item.name }` etc.
- Slots: use both `name` and `slot` attributes on `<slot>` elements

## Client Stack

- Alpine.js: `x-data`, `x-model`, `:disabled` etc. are preserved (not interpolated)
- HTMX: `hx-post`, `hx-target` etc. passed through
- Alpine attrs match `^(x-|[@:.]).*` and skip `{ }` interpolation
